Package com.google.closure.plugin.common

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ProcessRunner
    Abstracts away running a process so that steps that need to run other processes can be tested.
    ToolFinder<OPTIONS>
    Finds an executable file that can be used to compile source files.

    Class Description
    Cheats
    Some projects use package-private APIs to programmatically build compile configurations.
    CommonPlanner
    Common plan elements that are used by the various language type planners..
    CStyleLexer
    Lexes into C-style tokens.
    DefaultProcessRunner
    A process runner backed by ProcessBuilder.
    DirectoryScannerSpec
    Describes a set of files.
    GenfilesDirs
    The directories where code-generators should put their output.
    Ingredients
    Pools ingredients based on key.
    Ingredients.Bundle<I extends Ingredient>
    A bundle of ingredients.
    Ingredients.FileIngredient
    An ingredient backed by a file which is hashable when the file exists.
    Ingredients.HashedInMemory<T extends Serializable>
    Specifies how the compiler should interpret a group of source files and where to look for those source files.
    Ingredients.PathValue
    An ingredient that represents a path, and hashes to a hash of that path, not the content of the file referred to by that path.
    Ingredients.SerializedObjectIngredient<T extends Serializable>
    An ingredient back by a file dedicated to hold a serialized object of a specific type.
    Ingredients.StringValue
    An ingredient that represents a fixed string.
    Ingredients.UriValue
    An ingredient that represents a URI, and hashes to a hash of that URI's text, not the content referred to by that URI.
    Options
    Options for a compiler.
    OptionsUtils
    Utilities for dealing with plexus-configurable options bundles.
    SourceOptions
    Options that specify how to find sources.
    SourceOptions.SourceRootBuilder
    A plexus-configurable source root.
    Sources
    A group of source files split into test and production files.
    Sources.Source
    A source path.
    StableCssSubstitutionMapProvider

    TopoSort<I extends Comparable<? super I>,D extends Comparable<? super D>>
    Sorts depencies before dependers.
    TypedFile

    Words

  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    Asplodable
    Indicates that the annotated Options field is an array field that should have, at most, one value after the options have been asploded into clones that have every possible combination of asplodable field values from the ambiguous originating option set.
